    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-27T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="603"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/7960: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-27T22:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 27, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 28—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. My 102, January 22, 7 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d603fn13">Not printed.</note>
                    According to source heretofore reliable, the only definite decision reached at
                    the Berchtesgaden meeting<note n="14" xml:id="d603fn14">Meeting of Hitler and
                        Mussolini at Berchtesgaden, January 19, 1941.</note> was for German military
                    support in Albania to ensure prompt and successful conclusion of war against
                    Greece. Strong counteroffensive to be launched soon as weather permits; large
                    numbers Italian troops being called for service Albania, and German soldiers
                    already on way to Italian embarkation ports.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>The reference to German military support in Albania is unexpected as our
                    information up to now has been that German intervention in that sector was
                    unlikely.</p>
                <pb facs="0653" n="641" xml:id="pg_641"/>
                <p>Military Attaché is cabling on reported arrival during last few days of two
                    divisions German troops.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
